10:20- 11:50

            專題研討（I）
            Panel Discussion（I）
            家族企業之公司治理
            Corporate Governance of Family-Controlled Businesses

            說明：


            家族企業在亞洲國家已非常普遍，近年成長呈現停滯，與歐洲、北美之家族企業相較，亞洲家族企業之規模相對較小，因此面臨在國際市場上競爭資源及維持永續發展等挑戰。
            

            我國近年來家族企業接班與經營議題浮上檯面，如何傳承企業文化，增進企業價值，並為投資人與社會創造利益，凸顯家族企業接班計畫及公司治理之重要性。
            

            Background


            Family-controlled businesses are prevalent in Asia, but their growth appears to be stagnant. Compared to the size of family-firms in Europe and North America, Asian family-firms are smaller, which results in challenges for them to compete for resources in the global market and to maintain sustainable development.
            

            Recent controversial cases of successions and management fights of family-controlled companies drew our attention and revealed the importance of mapped out succession plans and corporate governance for family-controlled companies. Continuity of corporate legacy, value creation and stable growth are key components for family-controlled companies, and are beneficial to investors and society as a whole. 
            


            討論議題：
            亞洲地區家族企業公司治理之發展與機會為何？此類由家族高度掌控之公司，經營者及投資人應關註什麼議題？家族企業之公司治理又應與非家族企業有什麼不同？如何創造家族企業之價值與成長？
            
            Issues for discussion:
            What are the opportunities and challenges of corporate governance that Asian family-controlled businesses face?  What issues will be the top priorities for concern when managing or investing in companies with a high percentage of family ownership?  What are the differences in terms of corporate governance between family-controlled businesses and other types of enterprises?  What are the possible mechanisms for value creation and growth of family-controlled businesses?	
        

            主持人 Moderator
            Mr. Mitchell Van der Zahn
            Managing Consulting Partner
            WolfBar ESG Research Partners Singapore 

            與談人 Panelists
            Ms. Yoo-Kyung Park Director
            Sustainability & Governance Asia Pacific
            APG Asset Management Asia
            
            範博宏 教授
            香港中文大學財務會計學系
            Mr. Joseph P.H. Fan Professor 
            Department of Finance & School of Accountancy
            The Chinese University of Hong Kong

            鄭力軒 副教授
            政治大學社會學系
            Mr. Li-Hsuan Cheng Associate Professor
            Department of Sociology
            National Chengchi University

            蔡鴻青 發起人暨常務理事
            台灣董事學會
            Mr. Allen Tsai Founder and Executive Director
            Taiwan Institute of Director
        


11:50- 14:00
午餐 Lunch


14:00- 16:00

            專題研討（II）
            Panel Discussion（II）
            實踐股東行動主義
            Shareholder Activism

            說明：
            

            傳統公司治理議題多著重於提升董事會效能以降低代理成本，但早在1999年世界銀行提出之公司治理架構，已將公司治理分為內部管理及外部管理；經濟合作暨發展組織(OECD)於2015年發布G20/OECD公司治理原則，更將機構投資人之參與納入公司治理架構之一環。
            

            呼應我國公司治理藍圖之計畫項目「促進股東行動主義」，機構投資人之「盡職治理」係從市場面出發，運用機構投資人之影響力，連結資金提供者與被投資公司之長期利益，由市場參與者們積極帶動盡職治理文化，導引資金流向優質企業，提升被投資公司之治理品質、為大眾創造長期價值，同時健全投資產業之發展，創造三贏。
            

            Background
            

            Corporate governance has long been  focused on improving the effectiveness of the board function to reduce proxy costs. As early as 1999, the World Bank included further factors in its corporate governance framework wherein internal and external architecture of this field was expanded to include additional stakeholders. The G20/OECD Principles of Corporate Governance launched in 2015 have identified institutional investors as crucial participants in corporate governance best practices. 
            

            To obtain the goal of “promoting shareholder activism” as outlined in the “Corporate Governance Roadmap 2013, Taiwan launched the “Stewardship Principles for Institutional Investors “ in June 2016. The said principles value institutional investors’ input in the market and urge them to communicate with investee companies for long-term shared values.  The principles also serve as a catalyst which directs capital to companies that attach importance to good corporate governance. In a word, the principles try to create 3-wins—improve corporate governance, create long-term values for the public, and maintain sound investment. 
            


            討論議題：
            機構投資人盡職治理守則之源起？國際上的先行經驗及發展近況？各國機構投資人盡職治理守則之落實與展望？
            Issues for discussion:
            What is the origin of the Stewardship Principles? What are the latest developments and international practices? What are the applications and outlook for the Stewardship Principles in various countries?	
        

            主持人 Moderator
            Ms. Anne Molyneux
            Corporate Governance Consultant and Governing Board Member International Corporate Governance Network (ICGN)
            
            
            與談人 Panelists
            Ms. Pru Bennett Director 
            Corporate Governance in Asia-Pacific, Blackrock

            Mr. George Iguchi 
            Head of Corporate Governance
            Nissay Asset Management Corporation

            馮震宇 教授
            政治大學法學院
            Mr. Jerry Fong Professor 
            College of Law National Chengchi University

            蔡衷淳 副局長
            勞動部勞動基金運用局
            Mr. Chung-Chun Tsai Deputy Director General
            Bureau of Labor Funds

        



 











 

















